  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall aim of the project is to contribute to improved working and living conditions of workers and their dependants in the Bangladeshi garment and textiles sector. This will be done through capacity building of relevant partner organisations and of company management in supplier companies on productivity improvements through CSR management systems within the framework of UN Global Compact (UNGC) and UN Guiding Principles on Business and Human Rights (UNGP). This project is part of the greater ambition for CSR skills development in the sphere of Danish companies through a partnership between the three Danish fashion and textile industry associations supported by the Danish Business Authority as a pilot project until September 2015 and expected to be prolonged until 2018</narrative>
  </description>
